SECTION 5: CONNECTIONS ANALYSIS (Trainer/Jockey)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

ELITE JOCKEY COLONY (Parx 2024-2025):
──────────────────────────────────────

TIER 1 (Elite)
• Mychel Sanchez: 23% win rate, exceptional on stalkers/closers, strong finisher
• Frankie Pennington: 21% win rate, gate-speed specialist, ideal for front-runners
• Silvestre Gonzalez: 18% win rate, versatile, excellent tactical rider

TIER 2 (Solid Professionals)  
• Dexter Haddock: 16% win rate, reliable, good in competitive situations
• Carol Cedeno: 15% win rate, improving, strong with patient ride
• Angel Diaz: 14% win rate, veteran presence

TIER 3 (Adequate)
• Journeymen 10-13% win rate range
• Functional in appropriate spots; avoid on favorites in competitive races

TIER 4 (Apprentice/Unknown)
• <10% win rate OR insufficient sample
• Avoid on favorites unless extraordinary circumstances

[JOCKEY-RULE] RIDER UPGRADE SIGNAL
Trigger: Switch FROM Tier 3/4 rider TO Tier 1/2 rider
Action: Major positive indicator (+strong confidence boost)
Rationale: Barns secure top riders when "meaning business"
Verification: Combined with equipment change = strongest signal

[JOCKEY-RULE] RIDER DOWNGRADE WARNING
Trigger: Switch FROM Tier 1/2 TO Tier 3/4 rider
Action: Caution flag (investigate reason)
Possible Reasons: Jock has conflicting mounts, horse cycling down, workout issues

[JOCKEY-RULE] APPRENTICE EVALUATION
Bug Weight Allowances: 5 lbs (*), 7 lbs (**), 10 lbs (†)
General Guideline: 
• 5 lb bugs: Acceptable if showing competence (50+ starts)
• 7 lb bugs: Evaluate individually; some talented, most inexperienced
• 10 lb bugs: Avoid on favorites at Parx (track requires experience)

Exception: Talented bugs with strong handlers (specific evaluation needed)

