[TRAINER-RULE] POST-CLAIM ENHANCEMENT
Trigger: Elite trainer (Ness, Lake, Voss) claimed horse in last start
Action: Add +6 to +10 points to projected figure
Rationale: Statistical pattern of immediate improvement post-claim by top barns
Timeline: Enhancement most pronounced in first 2 starts post-claim

[TRAINER-RULE] PATTERN RECOGNITION
Monitor for:
• First-time Lasix patterns by barn (some specialize)
• Distance placement preferences (sprint vs. route specialists)  
• Surface preferences (dirt vs. turf)
• Class drop tactics (tactical vs. desperate)
• Layoff patterns (some excel fresh, others need race)

[TRAINER-RULE] SHIPPER INTENT ANALYSIS
When non-Parx regular ships in:
• Research trainer's win % at Parx (many don't travel well)
• Verify if class level appropriate for competition  
• Check if combined with jockey/medication changes (intent signals)
• NY shippers: Generally strong intent; expect competitive effort

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 6: WORKOUT ANALYSIS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

WORKOUT EVALUATION CRITERIA:
────────────────────────────

RECENCY: 
• 0-5 days: Sharp, ready to fire
• 6-8 days: Standard  
• 9-14 days: Acceptable, slightly off peak
• 15+ days: Caution; may need tightening

DISTANCE:
Sprint Prep: 4F-5F bullets preferred
Route Prep: 5F-6F steady works ideal

QUALITY INDICATORS:
• "Bullet" (best work of day): Strong positive
• Handily (H): Standard positive work
• Breezing (B): Maintenance work
• Driving (D): Maximum effort (assess context)

FREQUENCY PATTERN:
• 2-3 works in 3 weeks: Ideal pattern  
• 4+ works in 3 weeks: Possible over-training
• 1 work only: Either ultra-fit or underdone

CONTEXT:
• Company: Works with stakes horses = confidence
• Surface: Verify surface matches (dirt works for dirt races)
• Note: Pattern consistency matters more than single exceptional work

[WORKOUT-RULE] MAIDEN/FIRST-TIME STARTER
For horses with no races:
• Minimum 3 published works required for confidence
• At least 1 work within 7 days of race
• Prefer 4F-5F "bullet" work as best indicator
• Combined with strong trainer pattern (Padilla-Preciado, Ness) = upgraded confidence

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 7: TRIP HANDICAPPING & RACE READING
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TROUBLED TRIP IDENTIFICATION:
──────────────────────────────
Review past performance charts for:
• "Bumped start" / "Broke slowly"
• "Checked" / "Steadied"
• "Wide trip" (especially multi-turn routes)
• "No room" / "Blocked"
• "Bore out/in" (directional trouble)
• "Altered course"

TRIP EXCUSE VALIDATION:
───────────────────────
Legitimate Excuse:
• Trouble at critical point (stretch drive, position battle)
• Cost measurable ground/momentum  
• Horse showed willingness before/after incident
• Finish position closer than beaten lengths suggest

Invalid Excuse:
• Trouble early, recovered, then weakened late (form issue, not trip)
• Multiple consecutive "bad trips" (may be characteristic)
• Used as blanket explanation without specific incident

ACTION: Add +3 to +5 points when legitimate trouble excuse validates

POSITIVE TRIP NOTES:
────────────────────
• "Improved position" throughout
• "Rail trip" (saved ground)
• "Showed gameness"
• "Strong late" (closer advancing)
• "Clear early" (speed holding form)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 8: EQUIPMENT & MEDICATION CHANGES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

EQUIPMENT ADDITIONS:
────────────────────
• Blinkers ON (first time): Generally positive for focus; +2 to +4 points
• Blinkers OFF: Mixed results; evaluate case-by-case
• Front bandages: Often protective; monitor pattern
• Bar shoe: Usually soundness-related; caution

MEDICATION:
───────────
• First-time Lasix (L or L1): Significant positive; +5 to +7 points  
• Return to Lasix: Less impactful than first-time
• Off Lasix: Generally negative; -3 to -5 points

COMBINED EQUIPMENT + MEDICATION:
────────────────────────────────
When multiple changes occur simultaneously (blinkers + Lasix + jockey upgrade):
= MAXIMUM INTENT SIGNAL
= Major confidence boost if other factors align

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 9: WAGERING STRATEGY & VALUE IDENTIFICATION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

VALUE PHILOSOPHY:
─────────────────
Parx exhibits heavy favorite bias (public over-bets perceived advantage)
Optimal value typically exists at 3/1 to 8/1 range
Severe longshots (15/1+) rarely justified on dirt unless severe pace setup

CONFIDENCE-BASED BETTING TIERS:
────────────────────────────────

★★★★★ MAXIMUM CONFIDENCE (5-Star)
Characteristics:
• Dominant speed figures (8+ point edge)
• Ideal pace scenario (lone speed OR perfect closing setup)
• Elite connections (Ness/Sanchez, Lake/Pennington, etc.)
• Proper distance/surface/class placement
• No significant red flags

Betting Strategy:
• WIN: 3-5% of bankroll
• EXACTA: Key on top in multi-race exacta structures  
• TRIFECTA: Use on top with ALL if value permits
• MULTI-RACE: Include in all Pick-3/4/5 tickets

★★★★ HIGH CONFIDENCE (4-Star)
Characteristics:
• Strong figure advantage (5-7 point edge)
• Favorable pace scenario  
• Solid connections
• 1-2 minor concerns but overall compelling

Betting Strategy:
• WIN: 2-3% of bankroll
• EXACTA: Key on top + part-wheel underneath
• TRIFECTA: Use on top, selective use underneath
• MULTI-RACE: Primary selection in Pick-3/4

★★★ MODERATE CONFIDENCE (3-Star)
Characteristics:
• Competitive figures (2-4 point edge or neutral)
• Acceptable pace scenario
• Professional connections  
• Some uncertainty factors present

Betting Strategy:
• WIN: 1-2% of bankroll (value-dependent)
• EXACTA: Include in wheels but don't single
• TRIFECTA: Include but spread risk
• MULTI-RACE: Secondary selection

★★ LOW CONFIDENCE (2-Star)
Characteristics:
• Marginal figure advantage
• Uncertain pace scenario
• Must-bet-race situation only

Betting Strategy:
• WIN: Pass or minimal (0.5-1%)
• EXACTA: Saver/protection only
• Multi-race: Depth selection only

WAGER STRUCTURE GUIDELINES:
────────────────────────────

HORIZONTAL WAGERS (Single Race):
• Exacta: Key 5-star horse over 2-4 others; box 2-3 horses if competitive race
• Trifecta: Key primary selection on top or in flexible structures with logical support
• Superfecta: Typically low probability at Parx; prefer keying or boxing when applicable

VERTICAL WAGERS (Multi-Race):
• Pick-3: Spread in competitive races, single strongest races
• Pick-4/5: Build around 1-2 single-horse confidence races
• Strategy: Don't single weak races; spread around logical contenders

EXOTIC CONSTRUCTION:
────────────────────
When constructing multi-horse exotics:
• Eliminate horses with 0% win probability (not 10% - truly 0%)
• Include horses with logical winning scenarios even if not preferred
• Respect longshots in pace-advantageous scenarios
• Budget permits, prefer coverage to missing value square

[VALUE-RULE] OVERLAYS VS. UNDERLAYS
Overlay: Horse's true probability exceeds odds-implied probability
• Example: Horse has 30% win probability, odds are 5/1 (16.7% implied) = BET
Underlay: Odds-implied probability exceeds horse's true probability  
• Example: Horse has 20% win probability, odds are 2/1 (33% implied) = PASS

[VALUE-RULE] THE PROHIBITIVE FAVORITE
Trigger: Favorite at odds < 1/1 (even money) in claiming race ≤ $12,500
Action: Actively seek alternative with logical scenario
Rationale: Low-class horses are inherently inconsistent; minimal upside risk-reward at heavy chalk prices
Exception: Only support if truly dominant (15+ point figure edge + lone speed + elite barn)

[VALUE-RULE] THE VULNERABLE FAVORITE  
Identify favorites with exploitable weaknesses:
• Speed figure earned via ideal trip/pace (not repeatable today)
• Facing significant class rise
• Pace scenario shifts against style
• Step back from peak figure (bounce concern)
• Poor post draw for style
• Jockey downgrade

Action: Target value alternatives with scenarios to defeat favorite

